$ASRT the company closed the sale of Gralise gabapentin to Alvogen.

content: Trying out a shiny new drug for nerve pain called Gralise that has to titrate over 15 days to a whopping 1,800mg a day. To add to the fun it may not work until the 15 day mark, if at all.  Side-effects include depression, suicidal thoughts - basically, the same as working in IT.
